**[1844, 11-14] Ms.A.1.2.14.71**

Pugh, Sarah, to RDW. Triumph of Polk; political situation; cases of
escape of slaves; ... news of GT, D. O’C. and Father Mathew.

“... Fail not to tell me {u}what{/u} is the ‘O’Connell Rent,’
{u}where{/u} and {u}how{/u} collected, also to {u}what purpose{/u} the
‘Repeal Fund’ is applied. To building Catholic churches in America!!!
Very specific answers are requested for some persons, who wish to ‘speak
with authority’ on these matters.”


